  🟢  Green Hat — Full Product Design

  User Journey: Medical Tourism on Safar

  Step 1: SELECT TREATMENT
    "What procedure do you need?"
    → Cardiology: Bypass, Angioplasty, Valve Replacement
    → Orthopedics: Knee Replacement, Hip Replacement, Spine Surgery
    → Oncology: Chemotherapy stays, Post-surgery recovery
    → Dental: Implants, Root Canal, Cosmetic
    → Ophthalmology: LASIK, Cataract
    → Fertility: IVF, IUI
    → Cosmetic: Hair Transplant, Rhinoplasty
    → Wellness: Ayurveda, Detox, Yoga Retreat

  Step 2: SELECT CITY/HOSPITAL
    → Recommended hospitals for that procedure
    → Rating, accreditations (NABH, JCI), success rate
    → Estimated treatment cost range
    → Distance from airport

  Step 3: FIND NEARBY STAYS
    → Listings within 5km of hospital
    → Filtered for medical-friendly features
    → Caregiver rooms, wheelchair access, kitchen
    → Min stay duration matched to recovery

  Step 4: BOOK PACKAGE
    → Combined: Stay + Hospital pickup + Translator
    → Price: Treatment estimate + Stay cost + Services
    → Payment: EMI options, insurance partner links

  Step 5: POST-BOOKING
    → Pre-arrival checklist
    → Hospital contact info
    → Airport pickup scheduling
    → Recovery timeline

  India's Medical Tourism Strengths (design for these)

  - Cost advantage: 60-90% cheaper than US/UK for same procedures
  - Top cities: Chennai, Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore, Hyderabad, Kochi
  - Accreditations: NABH (National), JCI (International)
  - Key specialties: Cardiac, Orthopedic, Oncology, Dental, Fertility, Ayurveda

