  🟡  Yellow Hat — What to Build for MVP

  Tier 1: Quick Wins (enhance existing)

  1. Treatment picker — Add procedure-level search (not just specialty)
  2. Hospital detail page — Full profile with procedures, costs, success rates
  3. "Medical-friendly" badge on listings — filter by: wheelchair, kitchen, caregiver room, ground floor
  4. Package builder — Combine hospital + stay + services with total cost estimate

  Tier 2: Differentiators

  5. Cost estimator — "Knee replacement in Chennai: ₹2.5-4L treatment + ₹15K/week stay"
  6. Recovery timeline — "Post knee surgery: 7-10 days hospital + 14 days recovery stay"
  7. Caregiver mode — Book 2 rooms (patient + family), shared kitchen, pickup

  Tier 3: Growth Features

  8. International patient portal — Visa letter from hospital, airport pickup, translator
  9. Insurance partnerships — Pre-approved coverage, cashless treatment
  10. Telemedicine pre-consultation — Video call with doctor before travel

  ---
  ⚫ Black Hat — What to Skip

  - Don't become a hospital booking platform (that's Practo/Credihealth)
  - Don't guarantee treatment outcomes
  - Don't handle medical records (HIPAA/privacy nightmare)
  - Don't build a full EMR — just link to hospital systems
  - Visa processing — just provide information, not service

  ---
  🔴 Red Hat — Gut Feel

  - Treatment picker + cost estimator is the killer feature — patients Google "knee replacement cost
  India" and land on Safar
  - Hospital detail page builds trust — accreditations, photos, success rates
  - The "package" concept (treatment + stay + transport) is what makes Safar unique vs just booking on
  Booking.com
  - Caregiver accommodation is a real unmet need — families travel for medical treatment

